snippet.textDisplay: Independent behaviours are very complex to be programmed or self-learned by any machine. And sensors dont do the trick, you need to have sets of  behaviours already intalled in your robot. So if you start from scratch and attempt to program a robot by introducing small behaviours at a time you will simply never end to get finished the much bigger sets of behaviours required . On the other hand there is always hardware limitations to manage, store and process those requirements in realtime scenarios.
snippet.textOriginal: Independent behaviours are very complex to be programmed or self-learned by any machine. And sensors dont do the trick, you need to have sets of  behaviours already intalled in your robot. So if you start from scratch and attempt to program a robot by introducing small behaviours at a time you will simply never end to get finished the much bigger sets of behaviours required . On the other hand there is always hardware limitations to manage, store and process those requirements in realtime scenarios.
